3.00	Presidential_Decision_Directive	Presidential directive	Presidential Directives, better known as Presidential Decision Directives or PDD are a form of an executive order issued by the President of the United States with the advice and consent of the National Security Council. As a National Security instrument, the PDD articulates the executive's policy, carries the "full force and effect of law", and throughout the terms of presidents, have taken on various titles or intents towards national security policy.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/87/Nsdd.jpg/200px-Nsdd.jpg
